==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whinstone
<hw>Whin"stone"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Whin</ets> +
<ets>stone</ets>; cf. Scot. <ets>quhynstane</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
provincial name given in England to basaltic rocks, and applied by
miners to other kind of dark-colored unstratified rocks which resist the
point of the pick. -- for example, to masses of chert.
<xex>Whin-dikes</xex>, and <xex>whin-sills</xex>, are names sometimes
given to veins or beds of basalt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whinyard</ent>⟦br⟧
